com.att.research.xacml.api

Interface StatusDetail

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JaxpStatusDetail, StdMutableStatusDetail, StdStatusDetail

    public interface StatusDetail
    Defines the API for objects that represent XACML StatusDetail elements.
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.1 $
    Author:
    Christopher A. Rath

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
      Implementations of the StatusDetail interface must override the equals method as follows: Two StatusDetails (s1 and s2) are equal if: s1.getMissingAttributeDetails() is pair-wise equal to s2.getMissingAttributeDetails()
      java.util.Collection<MissingAttributeDetail> getMissingAttributeDetails()
      Gets the Collection of MissingAttributeDetail objects for this StatusDetail.
      StatusDetail merge(StatusDetail statusDetail)
      Gets a StatusDetail object that is the result of merging this StatusDetail with the given StatusDetail.

    • Method Detail

      • getMissingAttributeDetails

        java.util.Collection<MissingAttributeDetail> getMissingAttributeDetails()
        Gets the Collection of MissingAttributeDetail objects for this StatusDetail. If there are no MissingAttributeDetails an empty Collection must be returned.
        Returns:
        the MissingAttributeDetail objects for this StatusDetail or null if none.

      • merge

        StatusDetail merge(StatusDetail statusDetail)
        Gets a StatusDetail object that is the result of merging this StatusDetail with the given StatusDetail.
        Parameters:
        statusDetail - the StatusDetail to merge in
        Returns:
        a StatusDetail merging this StatusDetail with the given StatusDetail.
